  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_9' aria-label=\" Competition Commission of India versus Schott Glass India Pvt. Ltd. & Anr. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('9','2025','2025_5_1316_1359','2025INSC668'); ><font size='4'> <strong>COMPETITION COMMISSION OF INDIA<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>SCHOTT GLASS INDIA PVT. LTD. & ANR. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 5 S.C.R. 1316</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 668</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010006042025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : VIKRAM NATH<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, PRASANNA BHALACHANDRA VARALE</strong><br> Issue for Consideration I. Whether providing exclusionary volume based discounts, imposing contractual terms, refusing supply etc. will amount to abuse of dominant position? II. Whether the functional-discount / &ldquo;no-Chinese&rdquo; scheme (including the later TMLA arrangement) imposes conditions under Section 4(2)(a) and Section 4(2)(b) of the Act? III. Whether the LTTSA with Schott Kaisha produced a margin- squeeze proscribed by Section 4(2)(e) of the Act? IV. Whether Schott India tied or bundled NGA and NGC tubes, thereby breaching Section 4(2)(d) of the Act? V.<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 13-05-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 5843/2014</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Rejected</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('9','2025','2025_5_1316_1359','2025INSC668','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></